1 Corinthians 13:13 states: “And now these three remain: faith, hope and love. But the greatest of these is love”, Tis was the verse quoted by Ekiti State First lady, Bisi Fayemi, to celebrate her 30th anniversary with Governor Kayode Fayemi. The verse aptly connotes love has played a pivotal role in the sustainability of their nuptial union over the years. The two love birds could not hide their feelings as they gushed out on each other via social media, announcing the celebration of their 30th wedding anniversary. Kayode and Bisi Fayemi, could not ask anything more from their creator, as they have both witnessed the grace of God on their lives. The stylish Ekiti Governor and First lady have showed the world that love, endurance, perseverance, emotional support, faith, hope, long suffering and many more should be the foundation to sustain every union. Interestingly, they first met in the library at Obafemi Awolowo Universit, Ile-Ife as postgraduate students. They went ahead to marry and the union is blessed with a son. Kayode and Bisi attended different universities in Nigeria for their first degrees. While Kayode went to the University of Lagos, Bisi attended Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. Erelu Bisi and Kayode also went for further studies in the United Kingdom. Kayode got a Doctorate in War Studies from King’s College University of London, specialising in civil-military relations. Bisi received an MA in Gender and Society (1992) from Middlesex University. While Kayode delved into politics, Bisi has faced areas that interests her most: feminist activism, writing and policy advocacy. She serves on the Executive Boards of the African Women’s Development Fund, and the Global Fund for Women. She is also chair of the Advisory Council of the Nigerian Women’s Trust Fund and also serves on the Governing Council of Elizade University in Nigeria.